### Alternative Options for Country Flags

If you need more sophisticated country flags or the emoji flags aren't working well, consider these alternatives:

#### 1. `react-world-flags` Package

```tsx
npm install react-world-flags
```

Then use it like:

```tsx
import Flag from 'react-world-flags';

// Then in your component:
<Flag code={country.code} height="16" />
```

#### 2. `flag-icons` Package 

This package provides CSS flag icons:

```tsx
npm install flag-icons
```

Then import the CSS and use it:

```tsx
import 'flag-icons/css/flag-icons.min.css';

// Then in your component:
<span className={`fi fi-${country.code.toLowerCase()}`}></span>
```

#### 3. Image URLs from CDN

You can also use flag images from a CDN:

```tsx
<img 
  src={`https://flagcdn.com/16x12/${country.code.toLowerCase()}.png`} 
  alt={country.name} 
  width="16" 
  height="12"
/>
```

If you'd prefer to use one of these alternatives instead, let me know and I can update the code accordingly!

